resources.description:
The Kingdom of Bahrain is located centrally on the southern shores of the Arabian Gulf, to the right of Saudi Arabia and North State of Qatar, between latitude 25° 32 & 26° 20 North and longitude 50° 20 and 50° 50 East. 

And the Kingdom of Bahrain is an archipelago of 40 islands, a total area of 767.26 square kilometers. The largest island is the island of Bahrain, which includes the capital (Manama), representing 80.68% of the total area of the islands of the Kingdom. And connect with the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia through the King Fahad Causeway, which opened in November 1986.
